patch.description:
Update the custom data of an order.

The custom data must follow the following structure:

```json
{
  "groupName1": {
    "propertyA": "value",
    "propertyB": "value"
  },
  "groupName1": {
    "propertyB": "value",
    "propertyC": "value"
  }
}
```

If a `groupName` is set as null, it will be fully removed. If a property is set as null, only that property will be removed.
Values can be `string`, `number` or `boolean`.

**Tips:**
- For yes/no scenarios, it's recommended to use booleans instead of "yes/no" or 1/0 because booleans are shown in a localized user-friendly way in the Janis UI)
- It's not recommended that values are more than 100 characters long because they affect the usability of the UI for operation teams
- Double check that there is no native support for your scenario before using custom data.
